cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.LO, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the analysis of natural language assumptions and the development of a system of reasoning based on a fine-grained, hyperintensional analysis. It also involves the use of Transparent Intensional Logic (TIL) with its procedural semantics, which is a higher-order, hyperintensional logic of partial functions, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on automated reasoning systems and inference machines also makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper's emphasis on logic and inference makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
